description:
&lt;p&gt;An rare opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated dietitian, with experience in paediatrics, to join our friendly, dynamic paediatric dietetic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work with the children&#39;s and young peoples (CYP) diabetes team, to help deliver the Best Practice Tariff, alongside 2 other dietitians already working within this team. The team also comprises paediatricians, children’s diabetes nurses and psychologist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide dietetic care to patients referred via the antenatal diabetes team in the form via group education and a dedicated outpatient clinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also work alongside other band 6 paediatric dietitians and the lead dietitian for paediatrics, as part of the countywide Nutrition and Dietetics team. The successful candidate be responsible for managing a caseload of paediatric patients fed via home enteral feeding and general paediatric outpatient clinics in a variety of community based settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to staff training and CPD, participate regularly in student training and have a robust appraisal and supervisory framework. Mobile working has been been implemented within the Nutrition and Dietetic Service, further aiding our ability to work across a wide variety of settings including home, schools and acute hospital clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the basic salary, this post attracts a High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of basic salary (minimum payment of £1,034 and a maximum payment of £1,791) (pro rata where applicable).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full valid driving licence and access to a car to use regularly for business purpose is essential (unless you have a disability as defined by the Equality Act 2010).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Heidi Scott&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Lead Paediatric Dietitian&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: heidi.scott@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07760 990736&lt;/p&gt;
